<hr>
<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
For a <strong>named volume</strong> with an individual author:
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author&#8217;s surname, given name. <em>Title of Volume</em>. Vol. number of <em>Title of Multivolume Work</em>. Place of publication: Publisher, year of publication. 
</blockquote>
<br>
For a <strong>numbered volume</strong>:
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author&#8217;s surname, given name. <em>Title of Multivolume Work</em>. Vol. number. Place of publication: Publisher, year of publication. 
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
		<span title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Brown, Zoe</span>. 
		<em><span title="Title of Volume">Proverbs: Introduction and Commentary</span></em>. 
		<span title="Vol. number">Vol. 8</span> of 
		<em><span title="Title of Multivolume Work">The Goodman Companion to the Bible</span></em>. 
		<span title="Place of publication">London</span>: 
		<span title="Publisher">Goodman Institute of Bible Studies</span>, 
		<span title="year of publication">2056</span>.
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
		<span title="Author&#8217;s surname, given name">Smith, Claire</span>. 
		<em><span title="Title of Multivolume Work">Myths and Legends of the World</span></em>. 
		<span title="Vol. number">Vol. 1</span>. 
		<span title="Place of publication">Sydney</span>: 
		<span title="Publisher">Universal Press</span>, 
		<span title="year of publication">2056</span>.
	</div>
</blockquote>
